div.ab:
The fourth clime is the one in the centre of the island of Rhodes. Its cities are many. In view of their number, we 
mention a few that we know: Damascus, Homs, Caesarea, Aleppo, Manbiǧ, Apamea, Antioch, Harran, Urfa, Raqqa, 
Ras al-Ayn, Nusaybin, Syria (sic!), Baghdad and Arabia (sic!). Its territory extends from its beginning in the east on a 
line to the west. It extends from the land of ʾAsfār (= Hispania) and a part of the land of Africa up to the north of 
Sicily and the land of ʾAfrāṭi (= Crete) which lie opposite it, and (to) the land of Anqiyās (= Athens) from the land
of Rome, together with Cyprus and the great Asia. This clime is in the centre of the earth. That is why it is the best of
all countries in terms of its air and winds and the balance of its elements. That is why the people who live in it are wise
men and philosophers, star experts and masters of science. They conduct research into existing things (?) and the 
elements as well as precious stones. They have books in which the wonders, peculiarities and insights of the 10 
(sciences) are summarised:
(1) The knowledge of the spheres and the movements of the stars and the regularity therein; 
(2) knowledge of the science of geodesy; 
(3) the craftsmanship; 
(4) the calculation of what will be; 
(5) the knowledge of music - these are the enchantments of songs; 
(6) knowledge of the preparation of remedies to cure any animal of any disease - both the talking animals - that is, the 
human beings - as well as to cure the animals that do not speak, as well as the birds and others;
(7) knowledge of the manufacture of gold and silver through workmanship; 
(8) knowledge of magic and oracles; 
(9) the knowledge of the interpretation of speech by differentiating and making sure of the truthfulness of another's 
speech;
(10) the knowledge of the philosophers - that is the knowledge of the divine.
Those who live in this clime are famous for their wisdom and philosophy. They even surpass those who live in the 
third clime - in the fineness of their heart and their knowledge and in the pleasant air of their country. Its length and 
its width is as we said before.
